Diagnosis. The species is best differentiated from other members of the species group by the lobe ( l ) of the promere (
Figs 17 a–c
) and the characteristically enlarged finger-like posterior solenomere process ( psp ), the enlargement seen mostly from mesal view (
Fig. 17 b
).
